#module #cli #watch

> Click CLI and watchdog file watcher. Entry point for all user-facing commands.

eshp_cli.py — Click CLI and watchdog file watcher.

find_eshp_root() — walks up from cwd looking for an eshp/ directory.
  Falls back to creating ./eshp if none found.

EshpHandler (watchdog FileSystemEventHandler)
  on_created / on_modified → upsert_note + commit
  on_deleted               → delete_note + commit
  Only processes .eshp suffix files.

Commands:
  serve [--port 7842]   full sync + watchdog + local web server (cytoscape.js graph view)
  watch               full sync on startup, then watches for file changes
  new <slug>          creates skeleton note, opens $EDITOR, syncs on exit
  show <slug>         body + tags + outgoing/incoming edges
  search <query>      LIKE search, optional --tag filter
  scan <query>        broad search: FTS + tag names + 1-hop relation expansion (summaries)
  recall <slug> [-n N]  full note + N closest related notes (default N=1)
  tags                all tags with counts (bar chart)
  tag <tagname>       notes carrying a tag
  rels                all relationship types with edge counts (bar chart)
  edges [--rel REL]   all src --[rel]--> dst triples, optional rel filter
  graph <slug>        BFS tree, --direction forward|backward|both, --rel (repeatable), --depth
  stats               note/tag/edge counts
  init-skills <path>  copy bundled agent skill templates into path/
  summarise           compact graph summary for agent context injection

.part-of
-> architecture

.depends-on
-> store
-> parser
-> server
